   <category name='family-jewels'>

      <section name='assistant'>

         <para number='1' comment='talk to the assistant - hello'>
         The assistant bows and asks how he can be of assistance.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='job/work'>
         The assistant explains that it is his job to assist the shops patrons in making suitable choices for their purchases. "Having a human in the shop makes Family Jewels more than just an automated purchasing booth," he proudly explains.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='moon/selena'>
         "Working on the Moon is an interesting experience," he comments drily, "What with demands for protection money on one hand, and the Galactic Administration's regulations about 'illegal jewelry' on the other."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='galactic admin/GA'>
         He explains that the Galactic Administration has defined certain types of jewelry as 'illegal jewelry' which you can't buy without permission.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='illegal jewelry (1)'>
         He looks around furtively. "We used to sell so-called illegal jewelry - stuff that had been banned by the authorities. Mostly it was medallions, apparently people kept getting them caught in airlock doors. The Galactic Administration felt decisive action was needed so banned them.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='illegal jewelry (2)'>
         He rolls his eyes.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='illegal jewelry (3)'>
         "For a while we flouted the ban and sold them under-the-counter, but lately, the authorities have got more... well... authoritarian about the whole health and safety issue, so the owner decided to stop selling them."
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='family jewels'>
         "Family Jewels was established soon after the colony was opened. With the exception of the so called 'illegal jewelry' most of what we sell is very sophisticated." He waves a hand in the general direction of the displays.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='protection'>
         The assistant sighs, "Yes protection. I believe about thirty years ago the current owner's father declined to pay up. A few days later the shop suffered the only robbery it's ever had - and very nearly went bankrupt. Now we just look on the local mafia's payments as part of the cost of doing business."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='mafia (1)'>
         The shop assistant looks round nervously, "Although notionally run by part of the Galactic Administration, this colony is controlled by a local mafia. As long as you pay up they don't bother you, and they also make sure no other criminals bother you either."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='mafia (2)'>
         He shrugs. "It's not ideal, but at least it makes the Galactic Administration careful about what demands they make on the colonists, though they have got even more zealous about enforcing their 'illegal jewelry' regulations."
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='nomatch'>
         The assistant tells you that he can't help you, though he does, obviously, know about his work and the Moon colony.
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='bye'>
         The assistant wishes you a pleasant and fruitful stay on the Moon.
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='jewels/jewelry'>
         The assistant waves his hand round the shop. "What you see is the bulk of what we carry."
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='regulations'>
         "The Galactic Administration has regulations on everything it can get its sticky fingers near. The main ones that affect us are the ones relating to the so-called 'illegal jewels'."
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='buy'>
         The assistant looks at you in disbelief. "I really don't think you could afford any of the items we have on sale."
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='medallion'>
         "We used to sell medallions, although they were classed as 'illegal jewelry'. Sadly, we don't offer them for sale any more."
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='egg/easter egg'>
         "The Fedberge egg was a truly fabulous item," the assistant says reverentially. "Fedberge's designers came up with it as an exclusive keyring charm just for us, for a limited period only. It was the first time we offered an item designed to fit on the TenBrane keyring. It's been withdrawn now, but it was a huge success so we may look for more opportunities to sell accessories of this type."
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='fedberge'>
         "You must have heard of Fedberge, surely?" gushes the assistant. "They are Galaxy-famous. But then perhaps you don't usually move in the circles that can afford that sort... of..." he trails off, not wanting to embarrass you by implying you are not the kind of clientele they generally serve.
         </para>

         <para number='20'>
         "Fedberge have been in operation for centuries - I believe they even date back to before space flight. There's an entry on them in the Encyclopedia Galactica if you want to know more."
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='keyring/tenbrane'>
         "That was a new departure for Family Jewels. We had never dabbled in keyring charms before; we usually leave those kind of cheap gewgaws to Gallagher's. Of course, our Fedberge egg was in an altogether different class from their offerings." The assistant gives a little sneer, as he shows you his egg.
         </para>

         <para number='22' comment='gallagher'>
         "They like to think they are the top notch, with their strange gadgets and flashy jewelry, but really..." the assistant looks down his nose as he contemplates Gallagher's shop. "They weren't very happy when they found out we planned to sell something to attach to the TenBrane keyring, they seemed to think they had exclusive rights to that kind of accessory, but they were wrong and we had the lawyers to back us up."
         </para>

         <para number='23'>
         He gives a small smile of triumph. "Their complaints came to absolutely nothing in the long run. We sold the egg for the limited period we had intended, and it was a huge success. I am sure we'll sell more keyring charms in the future."
         </para>

