   <category name='food'>

      <section name='alhambra'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Alhambra - 908'>
         You stuff some money into the popcorn-selling droid's slot and in exchange receive a bag of popcorn so big you can hardly see over it. Any family that could get through this lot in one sitting must have more members than an army regiment! Still, you start munching and find the popcorn is so very more-ish that to your surprise you actually manage to finish the whole bag on your own.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         You can't afford to buy any popcorn. What desperate times must have befallen you!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='cafe'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - cafe - 390'>
         The waitdroid brings you a large plate of cannoli - Italian pastries stuffed with a sweet ricotta-cheese filling. Very delicious! It also pours you a cup of espresso coffee, which is very small but so strong you wouldn't want more than a few mouthfuls. The coffee taste cuts through the sweetness of the cannoli beautifully.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         You cannot afford to eat here - and this is not a good place to try and get away without paying!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='canteen'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Canteen - 854'>
         You seat yourself at one of the long tables and a dinner-droid appears. You pay it, and it carelessly places a tray full of food in front of you. The service is very slapdash, but the food smells just wonderful! You have been given an enormous plate of meaty lasagna and a big slab of pungent garlic bread. You stuff yourself until it's all gone, and feel so full you don't think you'll need to eat again for a week!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         You haven't got the groats to eat here, and if you try to get food without paying, the workers will toss you out - and they won't be gentle about it!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='casino'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Casino - 973'>
         A very glamorous humanoid waitress brings you a silver dish containing pretzels, which can be eaten easily one-handed without interfering with the gambling. You crunch your way through them and, surprisingly, feel as full and satisfied as if you had eaten a full meal. These pretzels have been specially formulated to give the energy to allow patrons to continue playing the tables for days at a time.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         The gambling here is far too rich for you, and so, it would appear, is the food - you can't even afford to buy yourself a bowl of pretzels.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='mario'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - marios - 847'>
         Mario's wife, Maria, appears from the kitchen, carrying a steaming plate of spaghetti and meatballs. Mario pauses in his conversation to watch out of the corner of his eye as you tuck in - once he sees you making the appropriate noises of enjoyment, he resumes his chat and everyone else in the bar relaxes. The food is, indeed, wonderful and you eat every last bit, leaving only a few smears of tomato sauce on the tablecloth (and your clothes).
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Not enuff groats'>
         A waitdroid points to the sign on the wall which says, "Please do not ask for credit, as a laser burn through the kneecaps often offends." You can't afford to buy a meal in Mario's, and only a fool would try to swindle the staff in here.
         </para>

      </section>

