      <section name='about'>

         <para number='1' comment='Info on navigation computer'>
         Arnie himself appears from behind a pile of junk and explains that these are 'surplus' ex-navy Mk 1 navigational computer software upgrades. The software will pilot your ship from the orbit of any planet with an exchange to the orbit of any other planet with an exchange.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='nav comp cont'>
         For you, as a special once in a lifetime deal, he will only charge 1,000ig. "A snip," he enthuses. There is only one problem...
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='nav comp cont'>
         In order to activate the program a special one-off code is needed, and to get that he will need a bribe from you to give a friendly navy programmer. Arnie thinks that a slithy tove would suffice to overcome the programmer's scruples.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='nav comp ends'>
         When you enquire why, if it is surplus, a bribe is needed, Arnie just shrugs. "Take it or leave it," he tells you, "it's not like you can get it anywhere else."
         </para>

