         <para number='1' comment='Get barbells - loc 719'>
         You bend down and grab hold of the barbells, then try to straighten up. The heavy weight won't move. You try harder, your muscles straining, sweat pouring off you, but they just will not budge. One final, titanic effort, and you manage to lift the barbells about a millimetre off the floor before your back gives out and with a spasm of agony, you let go and attempt to straighten your aching back.
